This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The paper also discusses the use of side information, which falls under the categories of network information theory (cs.NI) and source coding and channel coding (cs.SI). The paper also uses superposition coding, which is a common technique in wireless communication systems (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the capacity region of the broadcast channel, which is related to multimedia systems (cs.MM).
